      "source": [
        "# Continual Learning Demonstration (Illustrative)\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook demonstrates **why memory stabilization matters** in continual learning.\n",
        "\n",
        "We simulate two systems:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Baseline**: no memory; each task overwrites prior knowledge\n",
        "- **Razor (R4)**: confidence-gated memory reuse\n",
        "\n",
        "This is an **illustrative example**, not a benchmark leaderboard."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Setup"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os, sys, time\n",
        "\n",
        "repo_root = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \"..\"))\n",
        "if repo_root not in sys.path:\n",
        "    sys.path.insert(0, repo_root)\n",
        "\n",
        "from src.razor.memory_bank import RazorMemoryBank\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Setup complete\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Task Sequence\n",
        "\n",
        "We simulate three tasks learned sequentially:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Arithmetic\n",
        "2. Geography\n",
        "3. Logic\n",
        "\n",
        "Each task introduces new queries. The question is whether earlier tasks are retained."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "tasks = [\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"name\": \"Arithmetic\",\n",
        "        \"data\": {\n",
        "            \"2 + 2\": \"4\",\n",
        "            \"3 * 3\": \"9\",\n",
        "        },\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"name\": \"Geography\",\n",
        "        \"data\": {\n",
        "            \"Capital of France\": \"Paris\",\n",
        "            \"Capital of Japan\": \"Tokyo\",\n",
        "        },\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"name\": \"Logic\",\n",
        "        \"data\": {\n",
        "            \"If A and B are true, is A true?\": \"Yes\",\n",
        "            \"If A is false, is A true?\": \"No\",\n",
        "        },\n",
        "    },\n",
        "]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Baseline System (No Memory)\n",
        "\n",
        "Each task is \"learned\", but previous answers are forgotten."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "baseline_knowledge = {}\n",
        "baseline_accuracy = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for task in tasks:\n",
        "    baseline_knowledge = task[\"data\"].copy()  # overwrite\n",
        "    correct = 0\n",
        "    total = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    for past_task in tasks[: tasks.index(task) + 1]:\n",
        "        for q, truth in past_task[\"data\"].items():\n",
        "            total += 1\n",
        "            if baseline_knowledge.get(q) == truth:\n",
        "                correct += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "    acc = correct / total\n",
        "    baseline_accuracy.append(acc)\n",
        "    print(f\"After {task['name']}: accuracy={acc:.2f}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Razor System (Memory Stabilized)\n",
        "\n",
        "High-confidence results are retained and reused across tasks."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "bank = RazorMemoryBank(capacity=100, stability_threshold=0.95)\n",
        "razor_accuracy = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for task in tasks:\n",
        "    for q, truth in task[\"data\"].items():\n",
        "        bank.store(q, truth, confidence=0.99)\n",
        "\n",
        "    correct = 0\n",
        "    total = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "    for past_task in tasks[: tasks.index(task) + 1]:\n",
        "        for q, truth in past_task[\"data\"].items():\n",
        "            total += 1\n",
        "            val, conf = bank.retrieve(q)\n",
        "            if val == truth:\n",
        "                correct += 1\n",
        "\n",
        "    acc = correct / total\n",
        "    razor_accuracy.append(acc)\n",
        "    print(f\"After {task['name']}: accuracy={acc:.2f}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Comparison\n",
        "\n",
        "| Task | Baseline Accuracy | Razor Accuracy |\n",
        "|------|------------------|----------------|\n",
        "| Arithmetic | {:.2f} | {:.2f} |\n",
        "| Geography | {:.2f} | {:.2f} |\n",
        "| Logic | {:.2f} | {:.2f} |".format(\n",
        "    baseline_accuracy[0], razor_accuracy[0],\n",
        "    baseline_accuracy[1], razor_accuracy[1],\n",
        "    baseline_accuracy[2], razor_accuracy[2],\n",
        ")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Interpretation\n",
        "\n",
        "- The baseline system forgets earlier tasks as new ones arrive.\n",
        "- The Razor-aligned system retains prior knowledge via stabilized memory.\n",
        "\n",
        "This illustrates **why governed recursion and memory matter** in continual learning settings.\n",
        "\n",
        "For formal validation, see the unit tests and evaluator scripts in this repository."
      ]
    }
  ],
